&lt;br /&gt;
Every man has two educations - that which is given to him, and the other, that which he gives to himself.  What we are merely taught seldom nourished the mind like that which we teach ourselves.  Indeed, all that is mostly worthy in a man, he must work out and conquer for himself.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Jean Paul Friedrich Richter&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
~~~&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
At Virginia Falls, we stop for two nights.  The falls is certainly one of many highlights of the area, but there are other things to do and see here.  Most group member chose to climb Sunblood Mountain.  I chose the hike to Last Chance Harbor.  If by chance you are still in a canoe at this point, here you have one more opportunity to exit the river before it flows over Virginia Falls.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Here, near Virginia Falls, is also one of only two places within the prior park boundaries where floatplanes could land.  A number of people come to the park just to see the falls, from both the top and the bottom, and leave the same day.  There they see much, yet by choosing only one day, the also see so little.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In the 11 years since I have taken this trip, the boundaries of the park have expanded by over 6 times the prior size.  Indeed, I have seen so little of this park too.  &lt;br /&gt;
