&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/tripleman/4729191789/" title="Byzantine"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1337/4729191789_7eaa3782d9_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Byzantine" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The domes of the Hagia Sophia.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
There is a dictionary definition of Byzantine which means complex. In reality it comes from the maze-like political structures and elaborate ceremonies but, I'd imagine, some of it has to do with the architecture.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This might be a good example. Even having taken the photo myself, I still had to sit there for a minute to figure out what was going on here. I can't really explain it, so I'll leave it up to you. The overlapping domes are really strange and seem sort of impossible, but that's the way it is.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Beautiful, nonetheless.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
