&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/octopuzz/"&gt;octopuzz&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/octopuzz/4732883342/" title="Khiva - monument of Muhammad ibn Mūsā al-Khwārizmī"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1352/4732883342_b7b285b82f_m.jpg" width="240" height="160" alt="Khiva - monument of Muhammad ibn Mūsā al-Khwārizmī" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Abū ʿAbdallāh Muḥammad ibn Mūsā al-Khwārizmī (Persian/Arabic: أبو عبد الله محمد بن موسى الخوارزمي) (c. 780 – c. 850) was a Persian mathematician, astronomer and geographer, a scholar in the House of Wisdom in Baghdad. His &amp;quot;Kitab al-Jabr wa-l-Muqabala&amp;quot; presented the first systematic solution of linear and quadratic equations. He is considered the founder of algebra, a credit he shares with Diophantus. In the twelfth century, Latin translations of his work on the Indian numerals, introduced the decimal positional number system to the Western world. He revised Ptolemy's Geography and wrote on astronomy and astrology.&lt;br /&gt;
His contributions had a great impact on language. &amp;quot;Algebra&amp;quot; is derived from al-jabr, one of the two operations he used to solve quadratic equations. Algorism and algorithm stem from Algoritmi, the Latin form of his name.&lt;br /&gt;
(Source: Wikipedia)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/galoet/"&gt;Isabel Fagg&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/galoet/4764587777/" title="Kinderdijk"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4082/4764587777_4b3f6c6898_m.jpg" width="240" height="167" alt="Kinderdijk" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kinderdijk is situated in a polder at the confluence  of the Lek and Noord rivers. To drain the polder, a system of 19 windmills  was built around 1740. This group of mills is the largest concentration of old windmills in the Netherlands.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The windmills of Kinderdijk are one of the best known Dutch tourist sites. They were placed on the list of UNESCO list of World Heritage Sites in 1997.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/cinglesdeberti/"&gt;El senyor dels Bertins&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/cinglesdeberti/4764615835/" title="Pintures rupestres, Pedra de les Orenetes, la Roca del Vallès"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4123/4764615835_d89edde435_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Pintures rupestres, Pedra de les Orenetes, la Roca del Vallès" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;La Pedra de les Orenetes destaca per ser un gran bloc granític d'uns 8 metres de llargada i uns 3 d'amplada i d'alçada. Aquesta pedra és el contenidor d'unes pintures rupestres, que es concentren a la base, i diverses cavitats, una de les quals constitueix un abric de dimensions mitjanes. Des d'aquesta concavitat principal es pot travessar el bloc. En altres zones hi ha altres cavitats i punts erosionats amb representacions pictogràfiques.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
A les pintures s'individualitzen 32 figures que corresponen a traços corbats, serpentiformes, punts, figures femenines, cruciformes, barres, formes antropomorfes, quadrúpedes, ramiformes, representacions humanes i restes de pigment de difícil interpretació. Només s'interpreta el tema central de pintures, que són de color vermellós fosc.&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
Va ser inscrita dins la Llista del Patrimoni Mundial de la UNESCO l'any 1998 dins el conjunt d'art rupestre de l'Arc Mediterrani de la Península Ibèrica.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/874" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"&gt;Pàgina a la UNESCO World Heritage List&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Aquesta foto ha participat en el joc &lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/groups/enunlugardeflickr"&gt;En un lugar de Flickr&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?t=k&amp;amp;hl=ca&amp;amp;q=41.566833,2.324694" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"&gt;A Google Maps&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

