The Golden Circle is one of the main tourist routes from Reykjavik, visiting Þingvellir (Thingvellir), The Gullfoss waterfall and the geo-thermal area of Geysir.  Þingvellir is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.  It was  the location of the Athling, the world’s first parliament.  It is also the site of the rift between the North American and Eurasian tectonic plates.  &lt;br /&gt;
