&lt;p&gt;Buildings in Piazza Bra in Verona, Italy.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This is the Palazzo della Gran Guardia in Piazza Bra, Verona.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This is where we were to meet our holiday rep at the end of our day here before going back to the coach (we had to sit on the steps, which I didn't find comfortable).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The old town wall is to the left (as is the coach park where we were dropped off in Verona).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Palazzo della Gran Guardia, although similar in style to the work of Sanmicheli was built in 1610 by Domenico Curtoni. This palazzo, remained incomplete until 1820, is notable for its massive bulk, as well as the forceful design of the windows.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Information from a souvenir book I bought called &amp;quot;Verona: History and Masterpieces - English Edition&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

